& [DirectLMStudioEndpointManagerRunner] is the local manager runtime for Task_161
  + [spec_status] is active_runtime_contract
  + [runtime_module] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\sop_node\direct_lmstudio_manager.py
  + [runtime_demo] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\demos\direct_lmstudio_manager.py
  + [manager_transport] is direct LM Studio OpenAI-compatible endpoint
  + [default_endpoint] is http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1
  + [default_model] is openai/gpt-oss-20b unless WorkspaceState or a newer benchmark selects otherwise
  + [input_surface] is CompactManagerKernelBundle, CurrentFocalPoint, WorkspaceState, Runbook, WorkerPacketTemplate, and one selected Queue candidate
  + [context_stream] is DirectLMStudioManagerContextStream with one selected candidate, compact source slices, exact output shape, syntax latch, stale blocker handling, and outside preservation
  + [provider_probe] is GET /models before chat completion
  + [completion_call] is POST /chat/completions only when --send is explicit
  + [dry_run_default] is true unless --send is provided
  + [capture_output] is DirectLMStudioManagerRun preserving raw output and validation
  + [validator] is LMStudioManagerProposalValidation requiring all proposal fields, exact property marker, valid lane, outside, no launch claim, no mutation claim, and handoff threshold when OpenAI Codex is proposed
  + [observed_provider_result] is provider_available true, provider_called true, selected_model openai/gpt-oss-20b, validation_score 100, validation_band strong, integration_disposition accept_for_codex_review
  + [observed_review_disposition] is preserve_as_calibration_evidence because the manager proposed the already-completed runner build and left stale runtime_build_confirmation in outside
  + [allowed_surface] is build context stream, call LM Studio when explicitly requested, write context capture, write run capture, validate output, and report blocked or accepted disposition
  + [blocked_surface] is file mutation by LM Studio, shell commands by LM Studio, worker launch, OpenAI spend, commits, pushes, credentials, destructive actions, hidden daemon, and unrelated dirty files
  + [handoff_threshold] is repo mutation, implementation, uncertain authority, failing validation, specification ambiguity, high-risk action, hidden spend, credential boundary, or user-directed Codex escalation
  + [outside] is unsupervised loop, automatic dispatch, launch authority, direct mutation, hidden model state, broad manager competence, stale source state, and model training

  ? [use_when: the local manager should read a compact SOP stream and return one proposal or blocked note through LM Studio]
    = activate [DirectLMStudioEndpointManagerRunner]

  = must: default to dry-run unless --send is explicit
  = must: select exactly one queue candidate before prompt construction
  = must: extract selected candidate and model hints from full source files before prompt clipping
  = must: hide non-selected queue candidates from the compact prompt slice
  = must: preserve raw LM Studio output even when validation rejects it
  = must: reject missing fields, hollow fields, non-ASCII output, markdown output, missing property markers, invalid lanes, mutation claims, launch claims, and authority claims
  = must: treat accepted manager output as proposal-only until Codex review
  = should: use validation failures as manager prompt calibration evidence
  - never: dispatch OpenAI Codex workers from this runner alone
  - never: let provider reachability imply launch permission

